## 3. Performance Optimization

### 3.1 Lazy Loading

**REGLA**: Cargar visualizaciones pesadas solo cuando son visibles.

```javascript
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';

// ✅ BIEN: Lazy load visualizaciones pesadas
const WordCloudViz = lazy(() => import('./WordCloudViz'));
const TopicForceGraph = lazy(() => import('./TopicForceGraph'));

function InsightsDashboard() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading word cloud...</div>}>
        <WordCloudViz keywords={keywords} />
      </Suspense>
      
      <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading force graph...</div>}>
        <TopicForceGraph nodes={nodes} links={links} />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 3.2 Virtualization (Large Lists)

**REGLA**: Virtualizar listas de 100+ items.

```javascript
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';

function DocumentList({ documents }) {
  const Row = ({ index, style }) => (
    <div style={style}>
      {documents[index].filename}
    </div>
  );
  
  return (
    <FixedSizeList
      height={400}
      itemCount={documents.length}
      itemSize={50}
      width="100%"
    >
      {Row}
    </FixedSizeList>
  );
}
```

### 3.3 Debounce en Filtros

**REGLA**: Debounce filtros interactivos (input, slider) para evitar renders excesivos.

```javascript
import { debounce } from 'lodash';

function DashboardFilters() {
  const { updateFilter } = useDashboardFilters();
  
  // ✅ BIEN: Debounce input
  const handleSearchChange = useMemo(
    () => debounce((value) => {
      updateFilter('search', value);
    }, 300),
    [updateFilter]
  );
  
  return (
    <input
      type="text"
      onChange={(e) => handleSearchChange(e.target.value)}
      placeholder="Search..."
    />
  );
}
```

### 3.4 Memoization

**REGLA**: Memoizar cálculos costosos de D3 (scales, layouts).

```javascript
import { useMemo } from 'react';

function SankeyChart({ data }) {
  // ✅ BIEN: Memoizar layout Sankey
  const sankeyData = useMemo(() => {
    const sankey = d3Sankey.sankey()
      .nodeWidth(15)
      .nodePadding(10)
      .extent([[1, 1], [width - 1, height - 6]]);
    
    return sankey({
      nodes: nodes.map(d => Object.assign({}, d)),
      links: links.map(d => Object.assign({}, d))
    });
  }, [data, width, height]);
  
  // Render usa sankeyData
}
```

